[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = RandomizedSparsification","category":"page"},{"location":"#RandomizedSparsification","page":"Home","title":"RandomizedSparsification","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for RandomizedSparsification.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [RandomizedSparsification]","category":"page"},{"location":"#RandomizedSparsification._sparsify_context_data-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"RandomizedSparsification._sparsify_context_data","text":"_sparsify_context_data(A)\n\nCompute the necessary context data, A_1_norm, A_F_norm, P_ij and P_ij_cs (cumulative distribution on the matrix elements) for the sparsify randomized sparisification algorithm of A.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#RandomizedSparsification.r_ε-Tuple{Integer, Integer, Real, Any}","page":"Home","title":"RandomizedSparsification.r_ε","text":"r_ε(A, ε, [rank])\nr_ε(d₁, d₂, ε, rank)\n\nCompute the sufficient number of samples r required to achieve a given error tolerance ε in the sparsification of the matrix A (A in mathbbR^d_1 times d_2) in the expected value. Optionally use rank as an upperbound for operatornamesrank. The number of samples returned by this function is not necessarily the least bound for the number of samples needed for the error to bound to hold.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#RandomizedSparsification.rankrand-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"RandomizedSparsification.rankrand","text":"rankrand(d₁, d₂, rank)\n\nGenerate a random matrix of dimensions d₁ × d₂ with a rank rank.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#RandomizedSparsification.representation_error-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"RandomizedSparsification.representation_error","text":"representation_error(A, A_r)\n\nCompute the relative operator representation error between the original matrix A and the sparsified matrix A_r.\n\n\tfracA - A_r_textopA_textop\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#RandomizedSparsification.sparsify-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"RandomizedSparsification.sparsify","text":"sparsify(A; r, multithreaded=false, progress=false)\n\nSparsify the input matrix A using the randomized element-wise sparsification algorithm with r samples.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#RandomizedSparsification.srank-Tuple{AbstractMatrix}","page":"Home","title":"RandomizedSparsification.srank","text":"srank(A::AbstractMatrix)\n\nCompute the stable rank of the input matrix A.\n\nThe stable rank is defined as the ratio of the squared Frobenius norm to the squared spectral norm of the matrix.\n\n\tfracA^2_textFA^2_textop\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#RandomizedSparsification.ρ_s-Tuple{SparseArrays.AbstractSparseArray}","page":"Home","title":"RandomizedSparsification.ρ_s","text":"ρ_s(A::AbstractSparseArray)\n\nCompute the proportional sparsity of the input matrix A.\n\n\tfrac(ij)mid A_ij neq 0 (ij)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
